ver Sommer\n|-\n|2012\n| When the Ships Arrive\n| Holger Gutt\n|-\n|2014\n| Close to the sun\n| \n|}\n\n==Video albums==\n\n* ''Guano T-Apes'' (VHS, 1998)\n* ''Don't Give Me Names'' (VHS & DVD, 2000)\n* [[Guano Apes \u2013 Live|Live]] (DVD, 2003)\n* [[Planet Of The Apes / The Documentary (DVD)|''Planet Of The Apes / The Documentary'' (DVD)]] (2005)\n* ''Guano Apes \u2013 Live @ Rockpalast'' (2012)\n\n''Guano T-apes'' is a video that documents the development of the Guano Apes from their beginning. With band and individual interviews you get to know the members of the band better and experience curiosities and events from daily life in the music business. Along with the video clips, it contains lots of live material shot during the tours from Nov., 1997 through the summer of 1998. The video was directed by Richard Anjou and edited by Mathias Dohmbrinck.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{Guano Apes}}\n\n[[Category:Discographies of German artists]]\n[[Category:Guano Apes|Discography]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist discography\n|Artist = [[Guano Apes]]\n|Image = Guano Apes.jpg\n|Caption = Guano Apes live at [[Bospop]] (2009)\n|Studio       = 5\n|Live         = 1\n|Compilation  = 2\n|Singles      = 18\n|Video        = 5\n|Music videos  = 20\n|References = Yes\n|Ref link = References\n}}\n\n'''Guano Apes''' are an [[alternative rock]] band formed in 1994 in [[G\u00f6ttingen]], [[Germany]]. The group members are Sandra Nasi\u0107 (vocals), Henning R\u00fcmenapp (guitars, backing vocals), Stefan Ude (bass, backing vocals) and Dennis Poschwatta (drums, backing vocals).<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|last=Phares |first=Heather |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/p295621 |title=Guano Apes - Music Biography, Credits and Discography |publisher=AllMusic |date= |accessdate=2012-11-09}}</ref>\n\nTheir sound has been described as a fusion of metal, pop and rap.<ref name=\"allmusic\" /> Usually their music is labeled as [[alternative rock]] and [[alternative metal]].\n\nTheir discography consists of five studio albums, one live album, two compilation albums, eighteen singles and five video albums.\n\n== Studio albums==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Album details\n! colspan=\"9\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Sales\n! rowspan=\"2\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Media Control Charts|GER]]\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| AUT\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL]]\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Finland's Official List|FIN]]\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Federation of the Italian Music Industry|ITA]]\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[MegaCharts|NL]]\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| PRT\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Swiss Music Charts|SWI]]\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[Proud Like a God]]''\n* Released: 6 October 1997\n* Label: [[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]], [[Gun records|GUN/Supersonic Records]]\n* Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Compact Cassette|cassette]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 13\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 27\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 13<br><ref>{{cite web|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://swisscharts.com/showitem.asp?key=2708&cat=a |title=Guano Apes - Proud Like A God |publisher=swisscharts.com |date= |accessdate=2012-11-09}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n* WW: 3,000,000<ref>[http://www.deichbrand.de/site/bands/guano-apes/ Small item about Guano Apes at deichbrand.de ] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110909004941/http://www.deichbrand.de/site/bands/guano-apes/ |date=20